  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GWFP Mercon 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment consists of a participation of USD 40 million by IFC in a revolving credit facility (the Facility) in favor of Mercon Coffee Group (Mercon). The Facility aims at supporting Mercon for all its activities across the coffee sector value chain, from production and storage in countries of origin (Nicaragua, Honduras, Brazil, Guatemala, Vietnam) to transportation and commercialization in multiple destinations.   This project prioritizes improving farmers access to markets, access to finance, provision of technical expertise and climate-smart considerations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With its Leading Innovation and Farmers Traceability (LIFT) program, Mercon is committed to improve levels of productivity, ensure positive environmental and social impact, and raise the living standards of coffee communities in the region.</narrative>
  </description>
